It’s become clear that the culture of this restaurant is awful. The employees pretend as though customers are secondary and are in some way unnecessary. Service is always fast but the second you break them from their routine, all bets are off. Like most of the country, it is brutally cold outside right now. Upon sitting down to eat I took a peek at the thermostat, set to cool and an inside temp of 47 degrees. Needless to say, not a comfortable environment to eat lunch. I alerted them to this to ask if it could be switched to heat and told them it was too cold when not standing next to their ovens. The employee preceded to tell me they didn’t have heat, only A/C. Not that it was broke, that they physically didn’t have a furnace at all. A few moments later someone came to unlock and change the thermostat and almost immediately you could smell the distinct smell of heat kicking on for the first time in a long time. Why the need to lie? Why would you not want to create a comfortable environment for customers to eat lunch? It’s obvious Jimmy Johns is not known for having the best culture but to blatantly lie is taking it too far.
